  "text": "Tobacco is an exogenous source of reactive oxygen species (ROS) that subsequently leads to oxidative stress (OS). Tobacco products cause increase in free radicals and ROS production, which have a pathognomonic role in multistep carcinogenesis. They initiate mutagenic events by causing DNA damage that ultimately leads to degeneration of cellular components. Thus, free radicals and ROS stimulate malignant transformation and progression [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
